Explanation:

The documents provide evidence that Phase One and Mamiya have a close relationship, with Phase One investing in Mamiya in 2009 and becoming a 45% shareholder. In fact, one document even describes Mamiya as "'a Phase One company'" on its global website. Additionally, the acquisition of Mamiya Digital Imaging Company Ltd by Phase One is mentioned in several documents, which further supports the notion that Phase One has taken control of Mamiya.

Therefore, based on this information, it can be concluded that Phase One is indeed a subsidiary of Mamiya.

Instead, the relationship between the two companies appears to be one of partnership, with joint ownership and collaboration in product development and manufacturing processes.
